parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a sudden loss of power, leading to accidents, stalling, or leaving the driver stranded.

The failure of the battery can cause acid leakage, leading to corrosion of electrical components, brake lines, and other engine compartment components, which can result in accidents, stalling, or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the ignition coil can cause the vehicle to lunge while at idle, leading to accidents or loss of control.
The failure of the brake system can cause poor brake performance, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: corrosion of brake lines and hoses.
